# Investigation Playbook

A single reference file you can use for common cases.

---

## 1. Suspicious File Investigation

### File Details
- Name  
- Full path  
- Size  
- MD5  
- SHA1  
- SHA256  

### Checks
- Confirm location  
- Check digital signature  
- Review permissions  
- Check process tree  
- Compare hash on VirusTotal  

### Safe Indicators
- File is in a trusted folder  
- Signed by trusted vendor  
- Only one or few AV flags  
- Matches known version  

### Suspicious Indicators
- Found in Temp or AppData  
- Unsigned  
- Many AV flags  
- Executes at startup  
- Drops other files  

### Actions
- Isolate the file  
- Run scans  
- Keep hashes  
- Document behavior  

---

## 2. Remote Access Alert Review

### Alert Info
- User  
- Source IP  
- Destination IP  
- App name  
- Time frame  
- Country  

### What Triggered It
- Internal user  
- External destination  
- Remote-access tool seen  
- Not in exceptions list  

### Normal Use
- Chrome Remote Desktop  
- TeamViewer  
- AnyDesk  
- Vendor support sessions  

### Suspicious Use
- User denies activity  
- Late-night activity  
- Unknown tool  
- Repeated connections  

### Follow-Up
- Ask user  
- Check logs  
- Review destination owner  
- Add to exceptions if approved  

---

## 3. Network Connection Investigation

### Details
- Source  
- Destination  
- Ports  
- Protocol  
- App  
- Bytes in/out  

### Checks
- Reputation of destination  
- Geo lookup  
- Known service or CDN  
- User activity  
- Firewall logs  

### Safe Indicators
- Known provider  
- Expected port  
- Expected user action  

### Suspicious Indicators
- Foreign unknown IP  
- Large outbound data  
- User denies activity  
- Matches C2 patterns  

---

## 4. Process Investigation

### Process Details
- Name  
- Path  
- Parent process  
- Command line  
- User  
- Start time  

### Checks
- Digital signature  
- Hash lookup  
- Autoruns  
- Network usage  
- DLLs loaded  

### Safe Indicators
- In Program Files  
- Signed  
- Expected parent  

### Suspicious Indicators
- In Temp or AppData  
- Unsigned  
- Injects into others  
- Unknown network calls  

---

## 5. Email / PST Investigation

### PST Info
- File name  
- Size  
- Hashes  
- Owner  

### Tools
- pffexport  
- readpst  
- Outlook  
- pypff  

### Extracted Items
- Emails  
- Attachments  
- Contacts  
- Calendar entries  

### Things To Check
- Password reset mails  
- Financial emails  
- Phishing  
- Unknown senders  
- Suspicious attachments  

### Actions
- Export contents  
- Search subjects  
- Review headers  
- Flag suspicious items  

---

## 6. Quick Indicators of Compromise

### Host-Based
- Unknown startup items  
- Unexpected processes  
- Unknown scheduled tasks  
- High CPU network usage  

### Network-Based
- Outbound traffic to unknown IPs  
- Remote access sessions  
- Repeated failed logins  

---

## 7. Evidence Collection Checklist

- File hashes  
- File paths  
- Process list  
- Network connections  
- Event logs  
- User confirmation  
- AV scan results  

---

## 8. Response Steps

### Immediate
- Contain the host  
- Capture logs  
- Isolate suspicious files  
- Scan fully  

### Follow-Up
- Patch software  
- Reset passwords if needed  
- Update exceptions list  
- Document incident  

---
